node.text:
Trying something a bit different to show the process of how I make my videos! I've done vlogs in the past, but I've typically been too precious with them - setting up tons of cameras, microphones, and reading scripts. Who has the time for that?

So I gave myself the restriction that I could make this video with ONLY my cell phone. That way it wouldn't feel like it was getting in the way and I could keep the energy flowing while filming the actual trick.

Let me know what you think! I kept this under 5 minutes and actually really like it compared to the more proper vlog-style videos I've made.

node.text: There’s a shift happening online where companies have finally caught up to needing an endless amount of video content. And I’ve been lucky enough to be one of the people who is getting a lot of work making that video content. Just means I spend a lot of time grinding away in the studio without making much personal stuff 🤷‍♂️ Trying to balance having an online presence, being a production studio, and family (my baby’s the coolest) - usually the online presence falls to the side first. So if I ghost for a while or just pop up once in a while with some sponsored posts, it usually means life is just too hectic to do anything for myself. Kind of feels like I’m reaching a point where I need a team or more hands on deck to stay afloat with all my work - but not really sure how to make that happen. Anyways, things are good! Just not enough hours in the day to capture frames. Lots of really cool stuff happening offline as well that I can talk about at a later date ✌️

Headed to the beach today and packed all my essentials! I can take everything and everyone for a spin in the GLB. What do you pack for your beach days? 

#GLB #SUV #MakeSpaceforMore
